WEBVTT

00:01.410 --> 00:02.684
- I DON'T WANT TO GO BACK.
DO YOU WANT ME TO STAY?

00:02.790 --> 00:03.370
- YEAH.

00:03.480 --> 00:05.823
- IF MY WIFE WAS STILL ALIVE

00:05.930 --> 00:07.272
AND SHE ASKED ME
TO TAKE A TRIP TO ITALY,

00:07.380 --> 00:10.759
I'D BUY TWO FIRST-CLASS TICKETS
AND BEAT HER ASS TO THE AIRPORT.

00:10.870 --> 00:13.521
- I WAS READING THIS BOOK FOR
MAX, AND THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN

00:13.630 --> 00:15.689
I'M NOT READING ABOUT THE KID
ANYMORE, I'M READING ABOUT ME.

00:15.800 --> 00:17.552
- I WAS THINKING
THAT WE SHOULD

00:17.670 --> 00:18.694
TRY AND SEE
A MARRIAGE COUNSELOR.

00:18.810 --> 00:21.142
- I DON'T WANT TO SEE
A MARRIAGE COUNSELOR

00:21.260 --> 00:21.976
BECAUSE THE MARRIAGE
IS NOT THE PROBLEM.

00:22.090 --> 00:23.398
THE PROBLEM IS YOU.

00:23.500 --> 00:25.877
- I KNOW THAT IF YOU
LET THIS KID GO

00:25.990 --> 00:28.049
AND YOU DON'T SAY GOOD-BYE,

00:28.160 --> 00:30.082
YOU'RE GONNA REGRET IT
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

00:30.470 --> 00:33.473
[Joy Division's Isolation]

00:40.660 --> 00:43.618
- BUT IF YOU COULD
JUST SEE THE BEAUTY

00:43.730 --> 00:47.029
THESE THINGS
I COULD NEVER DESCRIBE

00:47.150 --> 00:50.278
THESE PLEASURES
A WAYWARD DISTRACT ION

00:50.390 --> 00:52.597
THIS IS MY ONE LUCKY PRIZE

01:21.560 --> 01:23.596
ISOLATION

01:23.700 --> 01:27.568
ISOLATION

01:27.670 --> 01:30.594
ISOLATION

01:30.710 --> 01:32.735
ISOLATION

02:05.640 --> 02:08.848
- HEY.
SCRAMBLED EGGS AND BACON.

02:08.950 --> 02:10.156
WHO WANTS BACON?
- I WANT BACON.

02:10.260 --> 02:11.773
- YOU WANT BACON.
YOU WANT BACON?

02:11.890 --> 02:13.460
- WHERE'S DAD?

02:13.580 --> 02:15.605
- DAD, UH, HAD TO GO TO WORK
VERY EARLY THIS MORNING, SO...

02:15.720 --> 02:18.883
- BUT IT'S SIGN-UP
FOR THE JOG-A-THON AT DROP-OFF.

02:19.000 --> 02:20.262
- I CAN SIGN YOU UP.
- NO, YOU CAN'T.

02:20.380 --> 02:21.756
DAD AND VICTOR ARE RUNNING
WITH TEAM COYOTE.

02:21.860 --> 02:25.375
YOU HAVE TO SIGN UP IN PERSON TO
GET YOUR OFFICIAL APRON NUMBER.

02:25.490 --> 02:26.036
- OKAY, WELL--
- HE PROBABLY FORGOT.

02:26.140 --> 02:28.131
- HE DIDN'T FORGET,

02:28.250 --> 02:29.820
AND I WILL SIGN YOU UP
AND I WILL MAKE SURE

02:29.940 --> 02:32.249
THAT I GET DAD'S
OFFICIAL NUMBER.

02:32.350 --> 02:32.793
- NO, YOU CAN'T.
I KNOW THE RULES, MOM.

02:32.910 --> 02:35.287
- HEY'
-DAD?

02:35.390 --> 02:37.142
- MOM SAID YOU HAD TO
GO IN TO WORK EARLY.

02:37.260 --> 02:38.352
- WE THOUGHT YOU FORGOT
ABOUT THE JOG-A-THON.

02:38.460 --> 02:39.256
- I WOULDN'T FORGET
ABOUT THAT.

02:39.360 --> 02:41.351
NO, I WENT OUT
TO GET DOUGHNUTS!

02:41.470 --> 02:43.461
- I CALL BOSTON CREAM!
- I WANT BOSTON CREAM!

02:43.570 --> 02:45.151
- BOSTON CREAM. THERE'S PLENTY--
- THAT ONE'S MINE.

02:45.260 --> 02:46.602
- ALL RIGHT,
YOU TAKE THAT ONE.

02:46.710 --> 02:48.462
- I'LL JUST TAKE IT
TO THE TABLE.

02:48.580 --> 02:51.435
I GOT IT FIRST.
- THAT'S THE ONE I WANTED.

02:51.550 --> 02:52.881
- COME ON.
- GO GET YOUR PLATE.

02:55.790 --> 02:57.678
- HELLO.

02:57.790 --> 03:00.896
- HEY. HANK.
- HEY.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.821
- NICE TO SEE YOU.
WHAT BRINGS YOU UP HERE TODAY?

03:06.320 --> 03:07.662
JUST LOOKING AROUND MY STORE.
I FOUND THAT.

03:07.770 --> 03:11.627
THAT SHOT I TOOK A WHILE BACK
OF BOB DYLAN.

03:11.740 --> 03:12.877
- OH, WOW!

03:12.980 --> 03:16.973
YOU TOOK THIS?
- YEAH.

03:17.090 --> 03:18.114
YEAH. IT WAS A WHILE BACK.
- WOW.

03:18.230 --> 03:21.085
THAT'S A GREAT SHOT.
- I THOUGHT, YOU KNOW,

03:21.200 --> 03:22.337
YOU COULD USE IT HERE

03:22.440 --> 03:24.089
AT THE RECORDING STUDIO
IS WHERE IT SHOULD BE.

03:24.200 --> 03:25.952
- WE CAN, FOR SURE.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

03:26.060 --> 03:27.049
THAT'S VERY GENEROUS OF YOU.

03:27.170 --> 03:29.263
- AH, IT'S NOTHING.
IT'S OKAY.

03:29.380 --> 03:34.067
YOU KNOW, WHILE I'M HERE,
SARAH TOLD ME THAT MAX

03:34.170 --> 03:36.821
WAS GOING TO THIS FAMOUS
ASPERGER'S DOCTOR.

03:36.940 --> 03:38.589
- YEAH, DR. PELIKAN.

03:38.700 --> 03:41.624
- YEAH.
YOU GOT HIS NUMBER HANDY?

03:41.730 --> 03:42.765
- WHY, IS SOMETHING
GOING ON WITH MAX?

03:42.870 --> 03:46.283
- NO, NO. NO, NO, NO, NO.
HE'S--MAX IS GREAT.

03:46.390 --> 03:47.459
HE'S DOING GREAT.
- GOOD.

03:47.570 --> 03:50.915
- YEAH. NO, NO.
IT'S--IT'S ANOTHER MA'I'I'ER.

03:51.020 --> 03:54.535
- OH, YEAH.
UH, YEAH.

03:54.640 --> 03:57.154
YOU WANT ME TO JUST FORWARD
HIS CONTACT INFO TO YOU?

03:57.270 --> 03:58.953
- YOU CAN JUST WRITE IT DOWN.

03:59.060 --> 04:01.745
- OH, OKAY. ALL RIGHT. SURE.
JUST WRITE IT DOWN FOR YOU.

04:04.960 --> 04:06.473
- [chuckles]
OH, MY GOD.

04:06.590 --> 04:08.478
I CANNOT BELIEVE YOU STILL HAVE
YOUR MODEL CONGRESS T-SHIRT.

04:08.590 --> 04:10.990
- I'M VERY PROUD
OF MY FAKE SENATE RUN.

04:11.110 --> 04:12.338
- [laughs]
WHAT?

04:12.450 --> 04:13.621
- THANK YOU. I'LL FOLD THIS.

04:13.730 --> 04:16.244
- DUDE, I THINK
IT'S TIME TO TRASH

04:16.350 --> 04:18.864
THE EVIDENCE OF YOUR
NINTH-GRADE ACCOMPLISHMENTS.

04:18.980 --> 04:21.255
- I HAVE TO AGREE WITH BERTO.
- WELL, I'M FEELING

04:21.360 --> 04:25.046
HARASSED, BUT STILL PROUD.
[phone rings]

04:25.160 --> 04:27.299
- IT'S MY MOM.

04:29.890 --> 04:31.983
HEY, MOM.

04:32.090 --> 04:36.299
YEAH. YEAH, IT IS.
IT'S SNOWING.

04:36.410 --> 04:38.264
IT'S FREEZING HERE.

04:40.240 --> 04:42.128
- YOUR GIRLFRIEND
HASN'T TOLD HER PARENTS

04:42.240 --> 04:42.854
THAT SHE DIDN'T
GO BACK TO TUFI'S?

04:42.970 --> 04:45.131
- UH, YEAH, NO.

04:45.250 --> 04:46.626
NOT YET.

04:46.730 --> 04:49.278
- DUDE, THIS IS GETTING WEIRD.

04:49.390 --> 04:52.735
IT'S BEEN TWO WEEKS.
HOW LONG IS SHE GONNA STAY?

04:52.840 --> 04:56.560
- YEAH, I DON'T--I DON'T KNOW.
WE'RE FIGURING THAT OUT.

05:00.020 --> 05:02.807
- OH.
- YEAH.

05:02.920 --> 05:06.151
- HOME, SWEET HOME.
- HOW'S IT FEEL?

05:06.270 --> 05:08.261
[chuckles]

05:08.370 --> 05:09.598
NO, NO, NO.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

05:09.720 --> 05:12.575
HOLD IT.

05:14.620 --> 05:18.306
ALLOW ME.
[both chuckle]

05:18.420 --> 05:21.799
- YOU REALLY MISSED ME, HMM?

05:21.900 --> 05:23.936
- YOU'RE TELLING ME.

05:24.040 --> 05:25.689
- I MISSED YOU TOO.

05:25.800 --> 05:28.143
- WELCOME HOME, SWEETHEART.

05:28.250 --> 05:32.289
- JUST THE SAME.
- WELL, UH...

05:32.400 --> 05:33.970
A LITTLE DIFFERENT INSIDE.

05:34.090 --> 05:37.639
all: SURPRISE!

05:37.750 --> 05:39.433
- WHOO!
- WELCOME HOME!

05:39.540 --> 05:40.984
- HI, SWEETIE.
[all talking]

05:41.090 --> 05:42.478
- YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL, MOM!

05:42.580 --> 05:44.980
- LOVE YOU. WELCOME BACK.
WE MISSED YOU.

05:45.100 --> 05:47.125
- MOSTACCIOLI!
HEY, THERE.

05:47.240 --> 05:48.684
- MWAH, MWAH!

05:48.790 --> 05:51.350
- MOSTACCIOLI.
- [laughs]

05:51.450 --> 05:53.179
- WOW.

05:53.280 --> 05:54.861
- AMBER, SWEETIE.

05:54.970 --> 05:56.380
- GRANDPA TOLD ME.
- MOM, SHE'S FINE.

05:56.490 --> 05:58.902
- IT'S OKAY.
MOM, MOM, IT'S FINE.

05:59.010 --> 06:00.284
- DID YOU BRING US PRESENTS?
- DID I?

06:00.390 --> 06:03.279
- YES!
- [speaking Italian]

06:03.390 --> 06:05.381
SWEETS FOR THE CHILDREN.

06:05.500 --> 06:07.047
- OH, NO.
OKAY...

06:07.150 --> 06:08.219
- YES!
- THAT'S IT--HEY, HEY.

06:08.330 --> 06:10.560
THAT'S FOR AFI'ER DINNER.
THAT'S DESSERT.

06:10.680 --> 06:11.567
THAT'S FOR AFI'ER DINNER.

06:11.680 --> 06:13.056
[overlapping chatter]

06:13.160 --> 06:14.434
- OH!
- I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

06:14.540 --> 06:17.509
I'LL HAVE FOUR NOW,
THEN FOUR PIECES OF BROCCOLI.

06:17.610 --> 06:20.306
THAT'S A DEAL.
NO, THAT'S A GOOD DEAL.

06:20.410 --> 06:24.130
[overlapping chatter]

06:24.240 --> 06:26.617
- IS IT GOOD TO BE BACK?

06:26.730 --> 06:28.129
- MM.

06:28.240 --> 06:29.719
- OH, MY GOSH!

06:29.830 --> 06:31.070
[chattering]

06:31.180 --> 06:34.388
OKAY, YOU HOLD ON TO IT.
WE'RE GONNA EAT IT LATER.

06:34.490 --> 06:36.799
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

06:36.910 --> 06:39.663
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

06:39.770 --> 06:41.772
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:41.880 --> 06:44.428
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:44.540 --> 06:46.747
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:46.850 --> 06:49.193
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:49.300 --> 06:51.120
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:51.230 --> 06:53.858
FOREVER YOUNG

06:53.960 --> 06:56.679
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:56.790 --> 06:57.950
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:58.070 --> 07:01.540
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

07:01.660 --> 07:03.753
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

07:03.870 --> 07:06.555
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

07:06.660 --> 07:08.628
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

07:08.730 --> 07:10.618
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:10.740 --> 07:13.311
FOREVER YOUNG

07:13.430 --> 07:15.591
MAY YOU STAY

07:15.710 --> 07:18.497
FOREVER YOUNG

07:24.090 --> 07:25.569
- [coughs]

07:25.680 --> 07:28.057
UGH, HEY, GUYS.
ADAM, CROSBY, IT'S AMBER.

07:28.170 --> 07:31.924
UGH. I WOKE UP WITH THIS
REALLY BAD COUGH, COLD THING.

07:32.030 --> 07:33.998
I THINK I NEED A COUPLE DAYS
TO REST IT OFF.

07:34.100 --> 07:38.412
I'LL CHECK IN SOON AND LET YOU
KNOW HOW I'M FEELING.

07:38.520 --> 07:42.968
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TALK
TO YOU SOON. BYE.

07:44.180 --> 07:47.832
[turns up volume]

07:47.950 --> 07:48.974
[rock/pop music]

07:54.400 --> 07:55.810
- HEY.

07:55.920 --> 07:58.980
AMBER JUST CALLED IN SICK.
- OH, NO. I HOPE SHE'S OKAY.

07:59.090 --> 08:02.571
- YEAH, ME TOO.
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

08:02.680 --> 08:04.022
- IS THAT WHERE
YOU'RE GONNA HANG IT?

08:04.130 --> 08:07.133
- YEAH. YOUR MOM WORKED
SO HARD ON IT.

08:07.240 --> 08:08.650
IT'S SO CUTE.
- OH, HEY, I FORGOT TO TELL YOU.

08:08.760 --> 08:09.920
HANK STOPPED BY THE OFFICE
THE OTHER DAY

08:10.040 --> 08:12.508
TO DROP OFF THIS BOB DYLAN
PHOTOGRAPH THAT HE TOOK.

08:12.630 --> 08:13.938
- OH, THAT'S NICE. SO NICE.

08:14.040 --> 08:15.769
- YEAH, THAT'S NOT WHAT
I'M GONNA TELL YOU, THOUGH.

08:15.870 --> 08:18.009
THEN HE ASKED ME
FOR DR. PELIKAN'S PHONE NUMBER.

08:18.110 --> 08:20.829
- OKAY. DID SOMETHING
HAPPEN WITH MAX?

08:20.940 --> 08:23.329
- NO, THAT'S WHAT I ASKED HIM.

08:23.430 --> 08:24.977
BUT THEN HE SAID
IT'S FOR ANOTHER MA'I'I'ER.

08:25.090 --> 08:26.011
- ANOTHER MA'I'I'ER.
AND YOU'RE JUST TELLING ME--

08:26.120 --> 08:28.463
- YEAH, AND I'M GUESSING
THE OTHER MA'I'I'ER...

08:28.570 --> 08:29.184
IT'S GOTTA BE HIM, RIGHT?

08:29.300 --> 08:32.326
HANK.
- WAIT A SECOND.

08:32.440 --> 08:34.328
- WHAT?
- YOU THINK HE HAS--WHAT?

08:34.440 --> 08:36.647
- I DON'T KNOW,
I MEAN, HE'S QUIRKY.

08:36.750 --> 08:38.638
- HE'S VERY QUIRKY.
- RIGHT?

08:38.750 --> 08:40.160
- AND SOCIALLY AWKWARD.
- HE'S VERY FOCUSED.

08:40.270 --> 08:42.329
HE'LL TALK TO MAX ABOUT LENSES
FOR HOURS.

08:42.450 --> 08:44.372
- HOURS.
- EXPOSURES FOR HOURS.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.653
CAMERAS FOR HOURS.
- HOURS, YEAH, I KNOW.

08:46.760 --> 08:49.206
- JUST LIKE BUGS.
- BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN HE HAS--

08:49.320 --> 08:52.699
- NO, BUT I CAN'T HELP
BUT THINK THAT IF HE DOES,

08:52.800 --> 08:54.142
THEN MAYBE MAX COULD
TURN OUT TO BE LIKE HIM.

08:54.250 --> 08:56.832
THAT'S NOT SO BAD.

08:56.950 --> 08:58.019
- NO.

08:58.120 --> 08:59.087
- HANK'S HAD A BUSINESS.
HE'S HAD RELATIONSHIPS.

08:59.190 --> 09:01.329
- FAILED RELATIONSHIPS.
- WELL, HE'S HAD THEM.

09:01.430 --> 09:02.397
- HE'S HAD THEM.

09:02.500 --> 09:03.637
WITH YOUR SISTER.
- YEAH, WELL...

09:03.750 --> 09:05.320
- THAT WAS OKAY.
- HE'S GOT A DAUGHTER.

09:05.440 --> 09:06.987
- HE HAS A DAUGHTER.
- RIGHT?

09:07.090 --> 09:08.887
- OH, YEAH.
BUT THEY DON'T GET ALONG.

09:08.990 --> 09:09.843
- HE'S A FATHER.

09:09.960 --> 09:11.541
WELL, SHE EXISTS.
- SHE DOES EXIST.

09:11.650 --> 09:14.266
- WHEN I LOOK AT THAT, THAT'S
A PRETTY BRIGHT FUTURE FOR MAX.

09:14.380 --> 09:16.894
- HMM.

09:17.000 --> 09:19.059
- SO...

09:19.170 --> 09:20.922
- ARE WE...
- WHAT?

09:21.040 --> 09:23.793
- HOPING THAT
HE HAS ASPERGER'S?

09:23.900 --> 09:26.698
- NO. NO, OF COURSE NOT.
THAT'D--

09:26.800 --> 09:28.108
I MEAN, MAYBE ON SOME LEVEL.

09:28.220 --> 09:31.667
- THAT WOULD BE UNBELIEVABLE.
- THAT WOULD BE GOOD.

09:33.400 --> 09:35.209
- WOW.
- YEAH.

09:37.920 --> 09:39.012
- HANK.

09:39.130 --> 09:40.848
- HEY.
- HI.

09:40.950 --> 09:44.090
- OH, YOU COULDN'T
FIND A PLACE FOR IT?

09:44.200 --> 09:44.950
- OH, NO, NO, NO, NO,
I LOVE IT.

09:45.060 --> 09:47.881
I JUST--
I WANT TO GET IT FRAMED.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.161
- YOU WANT ME TO FRAME IT?

09:50.270 --> 09:54.036
- UH, YEAH.
I INTEND TO PAY YOU FOR IT.

09:54.140 --> 09:55.619
- ALL RIGHT.
- BUT I WAS THINKING

09:55.730 --> 09:57.004
RED WOULD BE REAL BOLD.
KIND OF FUN.

09:57.110 --> 09:59.556
- NO, IT'S HORRIBLE.
HORRIBLE CHOICE, RED.

09:59.660 --> 10:02.834
YOU WANT TO GO SIMPLE.
BLACK. KEEP IT SIMPLE.

10:02.940 --> 10:04.976
- YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT,
I THINK THAT'S PROBABLY RIGHT.

10:05.080 --> 10:06.593
- YEAH.
- GOOD THING I CAME TO YOU.

10:06.700 --> 10:08.327
- ALL RIGHT, I GOTTA DO
A COUPLE THINGS HERE.

10:08.430 --> 10:10.284
I GUESS I COULD GET IT
TO YOU LATER TONIGHT,

10:10.400 --> 10:11.776
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

10:11.880 --> 10:12.869
- THAT'S FINE.
THAT'S FAST. THAT'S GREAT.

10:12.990 --> 10:13.297
- ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GET ON IT LATER.

10:13.400 --> 10:16.984
- OKAY.

10:17.090 --> 10:18.227
UH, HEY, HANK.

10:18.340 --> 10:19.784
JUST SO LONG AS I'M HERE...

10:19.890 --> 10:24.680
YOU DON'T HAPPEN
TO PLAY POKER, DO YOU?

10:24.790 --> 10:27.850
- YEAH, I PLAY POKER.

10:32.490 --> 10:36.108
[phone rings]

10:39.010 --> 10:40.045
- HELLO?
- HI. HOW ARE YOU?

10:40.150 --> 10:42.732
UNCLE ADAM SAID
YOU WEREN'T FEELING WELL,

10:42.840 --> 10:44.842
SO I GOT YOU
SOME CHICKEN SOUP.

10:44.950 --> 10:48.465
- OH. I'M NOT HOME RIGHT NOW.
- I KNOW YOU'RE NOT AT HOME,

10:48.570 --> 10:50.322
BECAUSE I'M STANDING
OUTSIDE YOUR DOOR

10:50.440 --> 10:51.190
WITH A BIG PILE
OF CHICKEN SOUP.

10:51.300 --> 10:54.269
WHERE ARE YOU?
- I'M AT THE DRUGSTORE.

10:54.370 --> 10:56.782
I'M JUST GETTING SOME MEDICINE
AND STUFF, SO MAYBE--

10:56.890 --> 10:57.993
[seagulls cawing]
- MM-HMM.

10:58.100 --> 11:01.376
OKAY, WELL, UM, SHOULD I
JUST WAIT FOR YOU, THEN?

11:01.480 --> 11:03.584
- UM...

11:03.690 --> 11:06.443
I'M NOT
AT THE DRUGSTORE, MOM.

11:06.560 --> 11:08.482
- UH-HUH.

11:08.590 --> 11:10.069
AMBER, WHAT'S GOING ON?

11:10.180 --> 11:13.627
- I DON'T KNOW.
I'M--I'M DRIVING AROUND.

11:13.740 --> 11:16.288
I'M AT THE BEACH RIGHT NOW.
- HONEY, WHERE?

11:16.390 --> 11:20.019
WHAT DO YOU MEAN DRIVING AROUND?
- UH, I DON'T KNOW, MOM.

11:20.120 --> 11:22.088
- LOOK, I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

11:22.190 --> 11:24.010
YOU SHOULDN'T JUST BE
OUT THERE DRIVING AROUND.

11:24.130 --> 11:26.337
LET ME MEET YOU SOMEWHERE.
WE'LL HAVE A SOUP OR SOMETHING.

11:26.440 --> 11:28.852
- I DON'T REALLY KNOW, MOM.

11:28.960 --> 11:30.814
I JUST NEED TO BE ALONE
RIGHT NOW.

11:30.930 --> 11:32.261
- AMBER, I JUST WORRY ABOUT YOU.

11:32.380 --> 11:34.098
YOU SHOULDN'T BE IN THE CAR
IF YOU'RE UPSET.

11:34.210 --> 11:36.405
- I'LL BE SAFE.
I PROMISE, OKAY?

11:36.520 --> 11:38.545
- YOU SOUND TERRIBLE.
THIS MAKES ME VERY WORRIED.

11:38.660 --> 11:39.274
JUST COME HOME.
- I GOTTA DO THIS, OKAY?

11:39.380 --> 11:41.177
BUT I'LL TALK TO YOU SOON.

11:41.280 --> 11:44.909
- I'M GONNA CALL YOU
IN AN HOUR.

11:46.050 --> 11:47.176
[sighs]

11:52.400 --> 11:54.846
- THOSE KIDS ARE WIPED OUT.

11:54.950 --> 11:56.053
- WELL, THEY WERE REALLY HAPPY

11:56.160 --> 11:58.811
THAT YOU WERE HOME TONIGHT
TO PUT 'EM TO BED.

12:11.350 --> 12:13.932
ARE WE JUST NOT
GONNA TALK ABOUT IT?

12:14.040 --> 12:17.692
- [exhales]
TALK ABOUT WHAT?

12:17.800 --> 12:21.861
- ABOUT WHERE YOU SLEPT
THE OTHER NIGHT?

12:21.980 --> 12:23.493
- SERIOUSLY?
- I HAVE A RIGHT

12:23.600 --> 12:26.216
TO KNOW WHERE YOU'VE SLEPT.
- YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T--

12:26.330 --> 12:29.879
I DIDN'T MAKE THIS MESS, JULIA.
I DIDN'T--I DIDN'T MAKE IT.

12:31.640 --> 12:35.019
- OKAY, I'M...

12:35.130 --> 12:36.677
BELIEVE ME, I WISH I COULD
GO BACK AND I COULD

12:36.790 --> 12:38.121
DO THINGS DIFFERENTLY,

12:38.240 --> 12:41.198
BUT I NEVER
JUST DIDN'T COME HOME.

12:42.450 --> 12:45.851
- I, UH...

12:45.970 --> 12:50.418
I WENT TO THE TRAILER
AND I GOT DRUNK AND PASSED OUT.

12:53.040 --> 12:56.419
- WHAT ARE WE DOING?

12:56.530 --> 12:58.213
- WHAT A'El'T/IWE DOING?

12:58.320 --> 13:02.461
I--YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

13:02.570 --> 13:06.631
I KNOW WUâ€™MT I'M DOING.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.775
I'VE GOT, UH,
AN 8:00 AM.

13:08.890 --> 13:10.289
I'M MEETING WITH PEET
TO GO OVER THE GROUNDS.

13:10.410 --> 13:14.198
AT 4:00 I'VE GOT TO TRAIN
WITH VICTOR FOR A JOG-A-THON,

13:14.310 --> 13:15.880
AND, OH,
THIS IS GONNA BE GREAT.

13:16.000 --> 13:16.716
POKER WITH YOUR BROTHERS
TOMORROW NIGHT.

13:16.830 --> 13:18.548
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO TO THAT.

13:18.650 --> 13:20.060
- I DON'T HAVE TO GO?
THAT'S NOT GONNA BE A BIG ISSUE.

13:20.170 --> 13:21.819
THE BRAVERMAN HOTLINE WON'T BE

13:21.930 --> 13:24.933
RINGING OFF THE HOOK
OR ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

13:25.040 --> 13:28.032
WE GOT ENOUGH RUMORS
FLYING AROUND.

13:28.150 --> 13:30.380
I DON'T KNOW, JULIA.

13:30.490 --> 13:32.560
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
WE'RE DOING WITH OUR LIVES.

13:32.670 --> 13:34.763
I'VE JUST GOT TO...

13:34.880 --> 13:39.362
[sighs]
JUST GOTTA GET ON WITH MINE.

13:53.100 --> 13:54.408
- GOSH, YOU'RE UP EARLY.

13:54.520 --> 13:56.863
- [chuckles]
IT'S 10:00.

13:56.970 --> 13:58.198
- RIGHT. WELL, OKAY.

13:58.320 --> 14:01.414
SO WHAT ARE WE GONNA
DO TODAY?

14:01.530 --> 14:03.486
- OH, UH, THIS GAL
I MET ON THE TRIP,

14:03.600 --> 14:05.556
SHE PINGED ME.

14:05.670 --> 14:08.116
SHE'S AT MOMA
FOR THE LUCIAN FREUD EXHIBIT.

14:08.220 --> 14:09.448
I KNOW IT'S BAD TIMING,
BUT SHE'S ONLY HERE

14:09.570 --> 14:13.802
FOR THE ONE NIGHT AND I WANTED
TO SEE THE SHOW ANYWAY, SO,

14:13.920 --> 14:17.014
YOU KNOW,
IF IT'S OKAY WITH YOU...

14:17.130 --> 14:20.190
- YEAH, YEAH, SURE, WELL,
I GOT STUFF TO DO AROUND HERE.

14:20.300 --> 14:21.119
IT'S OKAY, YEAH.

14:21.230 --> 14:22.265
- WELL, I'LL BE HOME
WAY BEFORE DINNER.

14:22.370 --> 14:24.782
I'LL FIX US SOMETHING LOVELY.

14:24.890 --> 14:28.405
- OKAY, WELL, HAVE FUN.
- OKAY.

14:28.520 --> 14:29.680
THANKS FOR UNDERSTANDING.

14:29.790 --> 14:32.031
- YEAH.
- ALL RIGHT.

14:32.140 --> 14:34.938
SEE YA. BUONGIORNO.

14:40.980 --> 14:41.833
- SO, YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN THAT WAY

14:41.950 --> 14:45.044
JUST FOR AS LONG
AS MY EARLIEST MEMORY.

14:45.160 --> 14:45.774
FIVE, SIX, WHATEVER IT WAS.

14:45.880 --> 14:48.940
I JUST KIND OF DECIDED

14:49.060 --> 14:51.437
VEGETABLES HAD TO BE
ON THE LEFT SIDE OF THE PLATE

14:51.540 --> 14:54.338
AND THINGS HAD TO BE
JUST A CERTAIN WAY

14:54.440 --> 14:57.193
OR I JUST COMPLETELY
FREAKED OUT.

14:57.310 --> 15:00.404
BUT I GOT BETTER, THOUGH.
OVER THE YEARS,

15:00.520 --> 15:02.272
I GOT BETTER.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.689
I MEAN, STILL,

15:04.800 --> 15:08.065
I BASICALLY HAVE TWO GEARS.

15:08.180 --> 15:12.105
I COMPLETELY SHUT DOWN
OR I GO FOR IT.

15:12.220 --> 15:14.279
TENACIOUS WAS THE WORD
THAT MY EX-WIFE USED

15:14.390 --> 15:18.144
TO DESCRIBE ME
WHEN WE WERE MARRIED.

15:18.260 --> 15:21.946
LATER IT WAS "BULLDOG."

15:22.050 --> 15:24.325
OR "BULLY."

15:24.440 --> 15:27.329
OR SOMETHING WORSE THAN THAT,
YOU KNOW,

15:27.440 --> 15:30.295
BUT, HEY,
I'M SURE A LOT OF PEOPLE

15:30.410 --> 15:33.197
WOULD DESCRIBE
THEIR EXES LIKE THAT.

15:33.310 --> 15:34.993
- [chuckles] YES, THEY WOULD.
- YEAH.

15:35.100 --> 15:37.159
BUT ANYWAY, SO I WAS READING
A BOOK THAT ADAM GAVE ME

15:37.280 --> 15:38.895
ON ASPERGER'S,
AND SOMETHING CLICKED.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.206
- HMM.

15:40.310 --> 15:42.039
- YEAH, I MEAN, I DON'T
WANT TO HAVE ASPERGER'S.

15:42.140 --> 15:45.029
YOU KNOW, COME ON,
IT'S JUST...

15:45.150 --> 15:47.357
ANYWAY, SO I TOOK THE TEST.
I TOOK THE TEST ONLINE.

15:47.460 --> 15:49.143
- OH, YOU DIDN'T SAY
YOU TOOK THE TEST.

15:49.250 --> 15:50.387
HOW DID YOU SCORE?

15:50.500 --> 15:52.491
- YEAH, I DIDN'T TELL YOU THAT?
YEAH, I DID.

15:52.600 --> 15:54.488
I SCORED, UH, HIGH. 40...

15:55.880 --> 15:57.495
42-ISH, YOU KNOW.
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

15:57.610 --> 15:59.328
BUT IT'S AN ONLINE TEST.
HOW ACCURATE CAN THAT BE?

15:59.440 --> 16:02.398
- IT CAN BE PRETTY ACCURATE.

16:02.510 --> 16:05.195
HOW DO YOU THINK
THAT THESE BEHAVIORS

16:05.300 --> 16:06.949
AFFECT OTHER PARTS
OF YOUR LIFE,

16:07.060 --> 16:08.573
BESIDES THE RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOUR EX-WIFE?

16:08.690 --> 16:13.036
- WELL, I HAVE A VERY
SUCCESSFUL BUSINESS, I-I...

16:13.140 --> 16:14.368
I HAD TO DOWNSIZE LAST YEAR.

16:14.490 --> 16:15.411
THAT'S BECAUSE I MOVED TO
MINNESOTA, THOUGH,

16:15.520 --> 16:18.341
TO BE WITH MY DAUGHTER.
- MM-HMM.

16:18.460 --> 16:19.529
- YEAH, I MEAN,
IT DIDN'T WORK OUT.

16:19.630 --> 16:22.929
EH...

16:23.050 --> 16:25.189
I GUESS, UH, I GUESS...

16:25.290 --> 16:27.667
THINGS COULD BE BETTER

16:27.770 --> 16:31.319
WITH RUBY, MY DAUGHTER.

16:33.160 --> 16:35.913
I GUESS I WANT TO KNOW
IF THERE'S A REASON

16:36.020 --> 16:39.228
WHY I'VE BEEN BLOWING IT

16:39.340 --> 16:41.683
WITH THE PEOPLE THAT I JUST

16:41.790 --> 16:46.272
CARE ABOUT THE MOST IN MY LIFE.

16:46.380 --> 16:49.998
YOU KNOW?
IF I KNOW, THEN MAYBE...

16:50.110 --> 16:53.967
MAYBE I CAN STOP BLOWING IT.

16:54.080 --> 16:59.006
YOU KNOW?
MAYBE I CAN CHANGE.

17:00.640 --> 17:04.872
- WELL...
ASPERGER'S IS NEUROLOGICAL.

17:04.980 --> 17:07.460
AND SOMETIMES KNOWING
THAT YOU HAVE IT CAN NOT ONLY

17:07.570 --> 17:11.085
BE A RELIEF BUT A PATH
TO ACQUIRING TOOLS

17:11.200 --> 17:14.920
FOR HEALTHIER SOCIAL
RELATIONSHIPS MOVING FORWARD.

17:15.030 --> 17:16.474
- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING, THEN?
YOU'RE SAYING THAT I DO HAVE IT.

17:16.580 --> 17:19.925
- IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO KNOW
IN AN HOUR.

17:20.030 --> 17:21.759
I'D NEED TO SPEND
MORE TIME WITH YOU,

17:21.860 --> 17:23.202
I'D HAVE YOU TAKE SOME TESTS.

17:23.310 --> 17:26.131
- LOOK, I KNOW, I KNOW,
YOU GOT YOUR METHODS AND ALL,

17:26.250 --> 17:27.649
BUT I'M NOT GONNA
SPEND THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS.

17:30.320 --> 17:32.834
JUST BALLPARK IT FOR ME,
YOU KNOW, GIVE ME--

17:32.940 --> 17:34.805
WHAT'S YOUR GUT ON THIS?

17:37.910 --> 17:42.700
- MY GUT...
[exhales]

17:42.820 --> 17:45.050
IS THAT IT'S A JUMP BALL.

17:45.160 --> 17:47.811
THE SPECTRUM IS VERY WIDE.

17:47.920 --> 17:49.888
I CAN'T TELL YOU THAT YOU
DEFINITELY HAVE ASPERGER'S.

17:49.990 --> 17:51.878
- I GOT IT. I KNOW, I KNOW.

17:52.000 --> 17:53.444
I KNOW WHAT JUMP BALL MEANS.

17:53.550 --> 17:56.587
YOU KNOW,
NOT THAT ASPERGER'S-Y.

17:56.690 --> 17:58.237
YEAH. I GET IT.

17:58.350 --> 17:59.658
CAN'T TELL ME THAT I DO,

17:59.760 --> 18:02.206
AND YOU CAN'T TELL ME
THAT I DON'T.

18:13.600 --> 18:14.919
- DREW.

18:15.020 --> 18:16.464
DREW, HOLD UP.
- HEY.

18:16.570 --> 18:18.083
- YOU'RE, LIKE, RUNNING.
- NO, I'M NOT.

18:18.200 --> 18:18.575
- AWAY FROM ME.
YES, YOU ARE.

18:18.680 --> 18:20.887
ARE YOU KIDDING?

18:20.990 --> 18:23.231
THE PROFESSOR DIDN'T EVEN FINISH
GIVING US DETAILS FOR TONIGHT

18:23.340 --> 18:24.432
AND YOU'RE, LIKE,
HALFWAY OUT THE DOOR.

18:24.550 --> 18:26.575
- I LEFT MY NOTES IN--
- HIGH SCHOOL GIRLFRIEND?

18:26.690 --> 18:29.784
IN YOUR DORM ROOM?

18:29.900 --> 18:32.107
LOOK, I TOLD YOU I DIDN'T
WANT A RELATIONSHIP.

18:32.210 --> 18:33.552
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE
AWKWARD AROUND ME.

18:33.660 --> 18:35.241
- [chuckles]
I'M NOT AWKWARD AROUND YOU.

18:35.350 --> 18:38.695
- OKAY, FINE.
'CAUSE I MISS YOU.

18:38.800 --> 18:41.246
- I MISS YOU TOO.

18:42.740 --> 18:44.879
- UM, SO I'LL MEET YOU
TONIGHT AT 9:00?

18:44.980 --> 18:47.562
FOR THE BUS.

18:47.670 --> 18:48.568
GRIZZLY PEAK.
ARE YOU DOING THIS HIKE TONIGHT?

18:48.670 --> 18:51.389
- OH, I HAVEN'T DECI--
IS THAT MANDATORY?

18:51.500 --> 18:54.389
- NO, BUT DREW, COME ON.
WE'RE TAKING ASTRONOMY.

18:54.510 --> 18:57.638
THE EARTH IS, LIKE, INTERSECTING
WITH A COMET TONIGHT.

18:57.750 --> 18:59.365
- YEAH.

18:59.480 --> 19:00.549
- YEAH, I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

19:00.650 --> 19:01.856
I'M REALLY BAD AT SCIENCE.
- YEAH, ME NEITHER.

19:01.960 --> 19:03.439
I'M GLAD TO HEAR
YOU DON'T EITHER.

19:03.550 --> 19:06.348
- YEAH, WELL, THERE'S GONNA BE
AN AWESOME METEOR SHOWER.

19:06.450 --> 19:07.610
I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE.

19:07.730 --> 19:11.109
HAVE YOU?

19:11.210 --> 19:13.792
- NO. THEY HAPPEN
EVERY YEAR, THOUGH.

19:13.910 --> 19:16.219
- OKAY.

19:16.320 --> 19:17.696
NO, THAT'S COOL.

19:17.810 --> 19:19.903
JUST GO DO LAUNDRY WITH YOUR
HIGH SCHOOL GIRLFRIEND.

19:20.020 --> 19:21.703
I GET IT.
- [sighs]

19:21.810 --> 19:24.699
- YEAH, BERTO MENTIONED
THE WHOLE LAUNDRY THING.

19:24.810 --> 19:26.050
IT'S PRECIOUS, THOUGH.
- YEAH, SOUNDS LIKE IT.

19:26.160 --> 19:29.152
HE'S NOT VERY LOYAL, BUT--
- NO, HE'S JUST IN COLLEGE.

19:29.270 --> 19:30.646
SO ARE YOU.

19:30.750 --> 19:32.854
COME ON, MAN.

19:39.170 --> 19:40.444
- YOU INVITED HANK.

19:40.550 --> 19:41.869
- YES.
- SARAH'S EX-BOYFRIEND HANK.

19:41.970 --> 19:43.517
HAN K-HAN K.
- YEAH. WHAT?

19:43.630 --> 19:44.938
WE'RE ALWAYS LOOKING FOR GUYS
TO INVITE TO THE POKER GAME.

19:45.040 --> 19:46.587
- YEAH, NORMAL GUYS.

19:46.700 --> 19:48.452
- WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

19:48.560 --> 19:49.595
- LOOK, I LIKE HANK,
DON'T PAINT ME OUT

19:49.700 --> 19:51.213
TO BE A BAD GUY
FOR STATING THE OBVIOUS.

19:51.320 --> 19:52.048
- WHICH IS WHAT?

19:52.150 --> 19:54.630
- THAT HE IS A LITTLE WEIRD.

19:54.740 --> 19:58.039
HE DOESN'T MAKE EYE CONTACT,
HE MUMBLES,

19:58.160 --> 20:00.390
HE IS NOT A GOOD
CONVERSATIONALIST.

20:00.500 --> 20:01.432
MINIMALLY,
WE CAN AGREE ON THAT.

20:01.540 --> 20:03.155
- WELL, NOT EVERYBODY
IS A MASTER

20:03.270 --> 20:04.430
OF SOCIAL INTERACTION,
CROSBY.

20:04.540 --> 20:05.984
- OKAY, I'M NOT ASKING
THAT HE BE A MASTER

20:06.100 --> 20:08.614
OF SOCIAL INTERACTION,
I'M JUST SAYING HE COULD BE...

20:08.720 --> 20:10.642
NOT A FREAK AND WE COULD
MAYBE ALL HAVE SOME BEERS

20:10.760 --> 20:11.920
AND SOME CIGARS...
- LOOK, CROSBY, I INVITED HIM.

20:12.030 --> 20:14.066
- JOKE ABOUT SEX...
- YOU INVITE GUYS ALL THE TIME.

20:14.170 --> 20:15.489
- YES, I INVITE GUYS
WHO GET IT.

20:15.590 --> 20:17.865
- HE GETS IT. HE PLAYS POKER.
HE'S COMING. THAT'S IT.

20:17.970 --> 20:19.449
DEAL WITH IT.

20:19.560 --> 20:20.584
- WHOA, HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
SO REWED UP ABOUT?

20:20.700 --> 20:22.725
- HE HAS BEEN
A GODSEND FOR MAX,

20:22.840 --> 20:25.729
AND I THINK THAT
YOU COULD BE A LITTLE NICER

20:25.840 --> 20:26.909
ABOUT INCLUDING SOMEBODY
WHO MIGHT BE SLIGHTLY DIFFERENT.

20:27.010 --> 20:30.218
THAT'S ALL.
THAT'S MY PROBLEM.

20:30.330 --> 20:32.491
[Cowboy Junkies'
Lost My Driving Wheel]

20:32.610 --> 20:39.152
- I FEEL LIKE
SOME OLD ENGINE

20:39.270 --> 20:45.266
THAT'S LOST
MY DRIVING WHEEL

20:45.380 --> 20:46.449
[turns up volume]

20:46.550 --> 20:51.271
FEEL LIKE SOME OLD

20:51.380 --> 20:51.994
ENGINE

20:52.110 --> 20:54.761
THAT'S LOST

20:54.870 --> 20:59.898
MY DRIVING WHEEL

21:00.010 --> 21:04.970
SOME OLD

21:05.090 --> 21:08.150
ENGINE

21:08.260 --> 21:10.911
THAT'S LOST

21:11.020 --> 21:13.773
MY DRIVING WHEEL

21:13.890 --> 21:16.950
[low conversation]

21:17.060 --> 21:23.306
I FEEL LIKE
SOME OLD ENGINE

21:23.420 --> 21:26.799
THAT'S LOST

21:26.900 --> 21:33.669
MY DRIVING WHEEL

21:39.500 --> 21:40.250
[door closes]

21:40.360 --> 21:41.349
- ZEEK?

21:41.470 --> 21:42.459
- YEAH.
- HONEY, I'M BACK.

21:42.570 --> 21:43.798
- I'M IN HERE. HEY.

21:43.920 --> 21:46.536
- OH, I AM SO SORRY
THAT I'M SO LATE.

21:46.650 --> 21:48.606
THE B.A.R.T. WAS ALL MESSED UP.

21:48.720 --> 21:50.290
- NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

21:50.410 --> 21:51.718
DID YOU HAVE FUN?

21:51.820 --> 21:55.711
- OH...

21:55.830 --> 21:56.819
LUCIAN FREUD IS JUST AMAZING.

21:56.930 --> 21:59.034
- HMM.
- HIS PAINTINGS,

21:59.140 --> 22:01.131
THEY'RE JUST SO RICH
AND LAYERED,

22:01.250 --> 22:03.241
VISCERAL, EROTIC.

22:03.350 --> 22:05.341
YOU'D REALLY LOVE HIM.
- HMM.

22:05.460 --> 22:06.688
- OH, SHOOT.

22:06.800 --> 22:08.529
I DIDN'T REALIZE
WE DON'T HAVE ANY FOOD.

22:08.630 --> 22:09.733
- YEAH.
WELL, THAT'S OKAY, MILLIE.

22:09.840 --> 22:11.250
- WELL, I COULD
THROW SOMETHING TOGETHER.

22:11.360 --> 22:12.395
MAYBE SOME TUNA FISH?
- NO, HONEY, SWEETHEART.

22:12.500 --> 22:13.114
WE'RE GOING OUT TONIGHT.

22:13.220 --> 22:16.599
I'M TAKING YOU TO DINNER.

22:16.710 --> 22:19.429
I MADE A RESERVATION
AT TIVOLI'S.

22:19.540 --> 22:22.464
- TIVOLI'S.
- MM-HMM.

22:22.580 --> 22:25.299
- IT'S MOLTO COSTOSO.
VERY EXPENSIVE.

22:25.410 --> 22:28.538
- YEAH. AND IT'S ITALIAN.

22:30.830 --> 22:34.926
JUST YOU AND ME.
AND I INSIST.

22:36.940 --> 22:39.079
- OKAY.

22:39.180 --> 22:41.239
- YOU CAN USE MY I.D. CARD JUST
TO SWIPE IN AND OUT OF THE DORM.

22:41.360 --> 22:42.452
- OKAY.

22:42.560 --> 22:43.800
- AND THEN IF THERE'S
ANY PROBLEM

22:43.910 --> 22:44.899
JUST CALL BERTO, AND HE CAN
SIGN YOU IN AS A GUEST.

22:45.010 --> 22:48.491
OH, WAIT, ALSO YOU CAN...

22:48.600 --> 22:50.875
UM, YEAH, YOU CAN
GET BREAKFAST WITH THIS.

22:50.990 --> 22:51.729
YOU JUST SCAN IT
AT THE DINING HALL.

22:51.850 --> 22:54.250
- OKAY, OR I HAVE SOME MONEY,

22:54.370 --> 22:56.463
SO I CAN JUST GET
A BAGEL OR WHATEVER.

22:56.580 --> 22:58.263
WHAT TIME ARE YOU GETTING BACK?

22:58.370 --> 23:00.406
- WELL,
WE'RE WATCHING THE METEOR,

23:00.510 --> 23:01.920
SO WE'RE JUST GONNA
STAY IN A HOTEL.

23:02.030 --> 23:03.065
'CAUSE IT'S LATE.

23:03.170 --> 23:04.853
- OH, YOU'RE NOT
COMING BACK UNTIL TOMORROW?

23:04.960 --> 23:08.680
- YEAH, NO.

23:09.000 --> 23:12.128
WHAT? WHAT'S WRONG?

23:14.250 --> 23:17.105
AMY, I'M...

23:17.220 --> 23:18.903
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU,
YOU KNOW?

23:19.010 --> 23:23.663
YOU'VE BEEN MISSING
A LOT OF CLASS.

23:25.430 --> 23:27.011
- I CAN'T GO BACK.

23:27.120 --> 23:29.680
- TO TUFTS?

23:29.780 --> 23:32.908
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
- I HATE IT THERE.

23:33.030 --> 23:36.545
I MEAN, THE GIRLS
ARE SNOBBY AND COLD,

23:36.650 --> 23:40.711
AND THE WEATHER'S DEPRESSING,
AND EVERYONE IS SO SMART.

23:40.830 --> 23:43.105
- SO ARE YOU.
- YEAH, WELL, NOT LIKE THEM.

23:43.210 --> 23:44.962
AND MY ROOMMATE IS AWFUL TO ME.

23:45.070 --> 23:47.868
- THE ROOMMATE THING
IS DIFFICULT.

23:47.970 --> 23:50.416
I UNDERSTAND.
I MEAN, LOOK AT THAT POSTER.

23:50.530 --> 23:51.792
- AT LEAST YOURS TALKS TO YOU.

23:51.910 --> 23:53.525
MINE DOESN'T EVEN
SAY HELLO TO ME.

23:53.630 --> 23:56.190
SHE ACTS LIKE I DON'T EXIST.

23:56.290 --> 23:59.669
- SWITCH ROOMMATES.

23:59.780 --> 24:01.941
- YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:06.370 --> 24:07.917
- WHAT?

24:09.480 --> 24:14.065
- I STARTED TO FEEL ALONE,
LIKE...

24:14.170 --> 24:17.230
LIKE SCARY ALONE.

24:22.350 --> 24:25.558
- SO YOU'RE NOT GONNA GO BACK?

24:25.670 --> 24:27.979
- I CAN'T. I CAN'T GO BACK.

24:28.080 --> 24:32.949
'CAUSE THE ONE THING THAT GOT ME
OUT OF THAT SCARY ALONE PLACE

24:33.050 --> 24:37.669
WAS YOU.

24:37.780 --> 24:41.329
YOU'RE THE ONLY THING THAT MAKES
SENSE TO ME RIGHT NOW.

24:41.440 --> 24:45.570
YOU'RE KIND OF ALL I HAVE.

24:52.210 --> 24:54.690
[knock on door]

24:55.970 --> 24:59.280
- HI! WHATHII SURPRISE.

24:59.390 --> 25:01.312
- HI.
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

25:01.430 --> 25:03.978
- UM...
- UH-OH.

25:04.080 --> 25:06.287
- I HAD A FRIEND...

25:06.400 --> 25:08.049
A FRIEND.

25:08.160 --> 25:11.288
BUT HE KISSED ME.

25:11.400 --> 25:12.981
AND--
- WAIT, HE KISSED YOU?

25:13.090 --> 25:15.149
- HE KISSED ME.

25:15.270 --> 25:17.545
- AND YOU DIDN'T KISS HIM BACK?

25:17.650 --> 25:21.609
- I DON'T--

25:21.720 --> 25:22.926
I PROBABLY
SHOULD'VE PULLED AWAY

25:23.030 --> 25:27.137
A HALF A SECOND EARLIER...
THAN I DID.

25:27.240 --> 25:29.720
BUT I C--

25:29.830 --> 25:33.345
IT'S N--IT'S--WE'RE NOT EVEN
FRIENDS ANYMORE, YOU KNOW?

25:33.460 --> 25:35.109
IT WAS JUST, LIKE, A...

25:35.220 --> 25:38.940
AND THEN I THOUGHT
THAT I SHOULD TELL JOEL.

25:39.050 --> 25:42.224
BUT THEN WHEN I TOLD HIM,
HE DIDN'T COME HOME.

25:42.330 --> 25:45.083
HE SLEPT AT WORK
IS WHAT HE SAID.

25:45.190 --> 25:49.365
- FOR HOW LONG?
- JUST FOR ONE NIGHT, BUT...

25:49.470 --> 25:51.438
I DON'T KNOW,
HIS BOSS IS ALSO--

25:51.550 --> 25:54.997
I DON'T KNOW,
IF YOU MET HER OR SAW HER...

25:55.100 --> 25:57.159
- DO YOU THINK
THERE'S SOMETHING GOING ON?

25:57.270 --> 25:59.830
- I DON'T--

25:59.930 --> 26:01.682
I HOPE...

26:01.800 --> 26:05.691
NOT,
BUT HIS REACTION WAS SO...

26:05.800 --> 26:07.973
DRAMATIC TO MINE
THAT I DON'T KNOW

26:08.080 --> 26:11.561
IF HE'S TRYING TO JUSTIFY
SOMETHING ON HIS END.

26:11.670 --> 26:13.706
- I THINK THAT MIGHT'VE
JUST BEEN A SHOCK

26:13.810 --> 26:17.701
THAT YOU LET A HALF A SECOND
TOO LONG GO BY,

26:17.810 --> 26:20.779
BUT I DON'T THINK
THAT IT'S IRREPARABLE.

26:20.880 --> 26:23.508
I THINK HE SOUNDS LIKE
HE GOT REALLY MAD, AND...

26:23.610 --> 26:25.123
- YEAH.
- THAT MAKES SENSE.

26:25.230 --> 26:27.539
AND HE NEEDED SOME TIME AWAY,
AND THAT MAKES SENSE.

26:27.650 --> 26:29.993
- I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.
THAT'S--

26:30.100 --> 26:31.510
THAT'S WHAT I'M HOPING.
I JUST--

26:31.620 --> 26:34.726
- JULIA, PEOPLE HAVE THEIR
UPS AND DOWNS AND MAKE MISTAKES,

26:34.830 --> 26:37.276
AND I JUST CAN'T IMAGINE
THAT JOEL WON'T

26:37.380 --> 26:40.178
FORGIVE YOU AND UNDERSTAND.

26:40.280 --> 26:45.001
ALL YOU HAVE IS NOT GONNA GO
AWAY BECAUSE OF HALF A SECOND.

26:46.150 --> 26:48.971
- YEAH.
I REALLY HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

26:49.090 --> 26:50.011
I'M GLAD TO HEAR YOU
SAY THAT.

26:50.120 --> 26:52.736
I JUST DON'T WANT HIM
TO LEAVE ME.

26:52.850 --> 26:54.158
YOU KNOW?
- WHO'S GONNA LEAVE YOU?

26:54.260 --> 26:56.433
NOBODY'S GONNA LEAVE YOU.

26:56.540 --> 26:59.407
- OKAY, OKAY. THANK YOU.
- NO.

26:59.510 --> 27:01.159
- GIMME A HUG.

27:01.270 --> 27:03.238
- YOU JUST MADE A LITTLE
MISTAKE, THAT'S ALL.

27:03.340 --> 27:05.308
- YEAH. THANK YOU.

27:05.410 --> 27:10.200
[blues music playing,
background chatter]

27:18.320 --> 27:22.598
- NOW, UH...[clears throat]
YOU BEEN OVER TO DONNIE'S?

27:22.710 --> 27:24.428
- NO, I HAVEN'T
BEEN OVER TO DONNIE'S.

27:24.530 --> 27:26.703
I HAVEN'T BEEN ANWVHERE,

27:26.810 --> 27:29.631
AS I'VE TOLD YOU
THE LAST 47 TIMES.

27:29.750 --> 27:31.980
JUST GOT HERE
A COUPLE HOURS AGO, SO...

27:32.090 --> 27:33.057
- [chuckles]

27:33.160 --> 27:35.401
YEAH, WELL, YOU GOTTA
GO OVER TO DONNIE'S.

27:35.510 --> 27:36.329
THEY GET GREAT BANDS

27:36.440 --> 27:39.614
AND THEY GOT
A MECHANICAL BULL.

27:39.720 --> 27:41.688
- OH, MY GOSH.
- [laughs] YEAH.

27:41.790 --> 27:44.918
'CAUSE YOU AND ME, YOU KNOW,
WE COULD GO OVER THERE

27:45.040 --> 27:48.077
AND DANCE AND RIDE THE BULL.
- MM. YOU KNOW WHAT?

27:48.180 --> 27:50.148
I THINK A MOVE IS A GOOD IDEA.

27:50.250 --> 27:54.357
IN FACT, I THINK I'M GONNA MOVE
DOWN TO THIS END OF THE BAR.

27:54.460 --> 27:56.906
AND YOU CAN STAY HERE...
- JASON.

27:57.020 --> 27:58.567
- JASON.
[both chuckle]

27:58.670 --> 27:59.591
IT'S BEEN SO NICE.

27:59.710 --> 28:02.804
YOU JUST HAVE
THE BEST LIFE, OKAY?

28:02.920 --> 28:04.251
- COME ON, NOW.

28:04.370 --> 28:07.055
IT SEEMS LIKE
I BOUGHT YOU THREE DRINKS.

28:07.160 --> 28:09.333
- OH, YOU BOUGHT ME
THREE DRINKS?

28:09.440 --> 28:12.409
SO YOU THINK I'M GONNA
HAVE SEX WITH YOU?

28:12.510 --> 28:14.137
WOW.

28:14.240 --> 28:15.992
DO YOU THINK
I OWE YOU SOMETHING?

28:16.100 --> 28:17.067
- NO.

28:17.170 --> 28:18.853
- THINK WE'RE GONNA
FALL IN LOVE TONIGHT?

28:18.970 --> 28:21.029
- ALL I'M SAYING IS I THINK
WE'RE GETTING ALONG, YOU KNOW?

28:21.140 --> 28:23.244
- THINK WE'RE GETTING ALONG?
THIS IS WHAT GETTING ALONG IS?

28:23.350 --> 28:26.456
I THOUGHT IT WAS MORE LIKE
I'VE JUST BEEN SITTING HERE

28:26.560 --> 28:29.688
LETTING YOU TALK AT ME
AND SAY A BUNCH OF STUPID CRAP

28:29.810 --> 28:33.018
THAT I DON'T CARE ABOUT
FOR, LIKE, TWO HOURS.

28:33.120 --> 28:35.566
THAT'S SORT OF WHAT I'M GETTING
FROM THIS WHOLE SCENARIO.

28:35.670 --> 28:38.252
- YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU'RE
A LITTLE BITCH, AREN'T YOU?

28:38.370 --> 28:40.679
- I'M A LITTLE BITCH?
I'M A LITTLE BITCH?

28:40.780 --> 28:42.338
- YEAH.
- I'M A LITTLE BITCH?

28:42.440 --> 28:43.668
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
- WHAT THE HELL?

28:43.790 --> 28:44.859
- WHAT NOW, JASON?
- WHOA, CALM DOWN!

28:44.960 --> 28:46.643
- LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE
THE BITCH NOW, DOESN'T IT?

28:46.750 --> 28:48.138
- JASON, CALM DOWN.
- THROW HER OUTTA HERE.

28:48.240 --> 28:49.719
- YEAH, JASON, CALM DOWN.
- AND YOU--I THINK IT'S TIME

28:49.830 --> 28:51.274
FOR YOU TO GO.
- IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

28:51.380 --> 28:53.132
I'M NOT THE ONE WHO'S HARASSING
EVERYBODY AT THE BAR!

28:53.240 --> 28:54.172
- AMBER!

28:55.450 --> 28:58.271
- YOU KNOW THIS GIRL?

28:58.390 --> 29:00.244
- YEAH, HE KNOWS ME.

29:00.350 --> 29:02.045
IT'S ALL RIGHT, GUYS.
I'M GONNA GO.

29:02.150 --> 29:04.835
YOU GUYS HAVE
A REALLY GOOD NIGHT.

29:04.950 --> 29:06.178
SHOULDN'T BE HERE ANYWAY.

29:06.290 --> 29:07.700
HEY, TAKE HER EASY,
WOULD YOU, JASON?

29:07.810 --> 29:09.869
GOOD LUCK, MAN.

29:14.300 --> 29:17.224
[sobbing]

29:20.240 --> 29:21.502
- HEY, AMBER.
- JUST LEAVE ME ALONE!

29:21.620 --> 29:22.575
- WHAT IS GOING ON?

29:22.690 --> 29:24.510
- I'M TRYING TO
JUST GET TO MY CAR.

29:24.620 --> 29:26.656
JUST WANNA GO HOME.

29:26.760 --> 29:28.136
- YOU'RE NOT DRIVING.
YOU'RE DRUNK.

29:28.240 --> 29:30.686
- I'M FINE!
I'M NOT DRUNK! JUST STOP!

29:30.800 --> 29:32.939
I'M TRYING TO JUST GO HOME.
- GIMME THE KEYS.

29:33.040 --> 29:34.450
- STOP IT!
YOU DON'T KNOW

29:34.560 --> 29:37.211
ABOUT DRINKING AND DRIVING,
YOU STUPID ASSHOLE!

29:37.320 --> 29:40.141
- LOOK, NO MATTER WHAT
YOU THINK ABOUT ME AS A FATHER,

29:40.260 --> 29:42.637
I AM NOT GONNA
LET YOU DRIVE DRUNK.

29:42.740 --> 29:44.219
- STOP IT!
IT'S REALLY IRONIC THAT

29:44.330 --> 29:46.946
YOU'RE TRYING TO TALK TO ME
ABOUT DRINKING AND DRIVING.

29:47.060 --> 29:48.391
JUST BACK OFF, OKAY,

29:53.030 --> 29:55.191
ALL OF A SUDDEN
YOU WANT TO TAKE CARE OF ME!

29:55.310 --> 29:57.687
YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT ME, MAN!

29:57.790 --> 29:59.098
JUST--JUST BACK OFF!

29:59.210 --> 30:01.724
SCREW YOU!

30:01.830 --> 30:03.991
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

30:04.110 --> 30:06.032
THIS IS YOUR FAULT ANYWAY!

30:06.140 --> 30:07.960
- MY FAULT?
HOW IS IT MY FAULT?

30:08.080 --> 30:09.240
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON!

30:09.350 --> 30:13.628
- IT'S YOUR FAULT! OKAY?
BECAUSE MY FIANCE LEI-T ME!

30:13.740 --> 30:17.801
AND I LOVED HIM,
AND NOW HE'S GONE, OKAY?

30:17.910 --> 30:19.389
- SO YOU'RE MAD AT ME
BECAUSE YOU THINK

30:19.500 --> 30:20.319
YOU'RE GONNA MARRY
SOMEBODY LIKE ME, RIGHT?

30:20.430 --> 30:23.911
- NO. NO, THAT'S NOT WHY!

30:24.020 --> 30:26.432
- WHY?
- IT'S BECAUSE--BECAUSE YOU'RE--

30:26.540 --> 30:30.715
BECAUSE I'M AFRAID I'M--

30:30.820 --> 30:33.539
I'M LIKE YOU!

30:33.650 --> 30:36.790
I'M AFRAID
I'M EXACTLY LIKE YOU,

30:36.900 --> 30:41.553
IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE
AT SOME STUPID BAR.

30:41.660 --> 30:44.629
[sobbing]

30:55.060 --> 30:58.268
- I WAS STANDING
IN THE PALAZZO COMUNALE

30:58.370 --> 31:01.919
IN MONTEPULCIANO
WHEN IT HIT ME...

31:02.030 --> 31:05.477
THE GRANDIOSITY OF THE WORLD.

31:08.590 --> 31:10.376
ITS SHEER BEAUTY...

31:10.480 --> 31:14.109
MAGNITUDE...
HOW LITTLE I KNOW OF IT.

31:14.210 --> 31:17.384
HOW MUCH I WANT TO KNOW.

31:17.490 --> 31:20.379
- YEAH, I DON'T--IT'S KIND OF
A CRAPSHOOT, THOUGH, ISN'T IT?

31:20.490 --> 31:23.186
I MEAN, YOU'RE STANDING THERE
IN ALL THESE BEAUTIFUL PLACES,

31:23.290 --> 31:24.939
AND THEN AT THE SAME TIME,

31:25.050 --> 31:26.460
YOU'RE MISSING AMBER'S BREAKUP

31:26.570 --> 31:29.368
AND, YOU KNOW,
KRISTINA'S ELECTION THING.

31:29.470 --> 31:32.018
- WELL, THAT'S TRUE.

31:32.130 --> 31:33.358
HOW'D SHE TAKE IT?

31:33.470 --> 31:34.778
HOW'D SHE TAKE THE LOSS?

31:34.890 --> 31:37.097
- WELL, SHE WAS BEAUTIFUL.
I MEAN, SHE...

31:37.200 --> 31:39.373
SHE JUST
HANDLED IT WITH GRACE.

31:39.480 --> 31:40.640
- OF COURSE.

31:40.760 --> 31:41.954
- I MEAN,
SHE'S GONNA DO SOMETHING.

31:42.070 --> 31:43.822
- YEAH, I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

31:43.930 --> 31:45.511
AND THAT'S THE OTHER THING
ABOUT GOING AWAY.

31:45.620 --> 31:47.417
YOU REALIZE THAT LIFE
JUST GOES ON WITHOUT YOU,

31:47.520 --> 31:48.657
YOU'RE NOT REALLY NEEDED.

31:48.760 --> 31:50.455
- OH, COME ON.

31:50.560 --> 31:53.859
HONEY, YOU ARE SO NEEDED.
- YEAH, WELL...

31:53.980 --> 31:57.495
- NO, I DON'T MEAN IT
IN A BAD WAY, IT'S...

31:57.600 --> 32:01.878
IT'S LIBERATING.
MEANS I CAN GO AWAY AGAIN.

32:01.980 --> 32:04.699
- AGAIN? YOU'RE GONNA--

32:04.810 --> 32:06.016
YOU'RE GOING AWAY AGAIN?

32:06.130 --> 32:07.461
- WELL, THE CLASS
IS TAKING A TRIP TO FRANCE

32:07.580 --> 32:10.128
IN THREE MONTHS IN APRIL.

32:12.200 --> 32:14.407
- THREE MONTHS?

32:14.510 --> 32:18.094
- [sighs] I KNOW THIS IS
A BIG CHANGE FOR US.

32:18.210 --> 32:20.542
AND I UNDERSTAND WHY YOU DON'T
WANT TO SELL THE HOUSE.

32:20.660 --> 32:21.752
I REALLY DO.

32:21.870 --> 32:23.417
BUT I'M NOT READY
TO GIVE UP MY DREAM.

32:23.520 --> 32:27.001
I'M JUST NOT.

32:27.110 --> 32:30.694
BECAUSE IT'S MY DREAM.

32:30.810 --> 32:33.597
AND, UM, I THOUGHT ABOUT IT
A LOT WHEN I WAS AWAY,

32:33.710 --> 32:38.226
AND I FIGURED OUT THAT IF
I WORK AT THE STUDIO PART TIME,

32:38.330 --> 32:41.390
I COULD PROBABLY
MAKE ABOUT $300 A WEEK,

32:41.510 --> 32:45.367
WHICH MEANS AT THE END
OF THREE MONTHS I WOULD HAVE

32:45.480 --> 32:48.051
ENOUGH TO COVER
MOST OF THE COST OF THE TRIP.

32:48.170 --> 32:51.333
- WELL, THAT--THAT IS--

32:51.450 --> 32:54.726
OKAY. WELL, YOU GOT IT
ALL FIGURED OUT.

32:54.830 --> 32:57.344
AND THAT'S GOOD.

32:57.450 --> 32:58.178
- YEAH.

32:58.280 --> 33:01.340
[dinner music playing]

33:05.770 --> 33:08.147
[phone ringing]

33:09.330 --> 33:12.151
- [sighs]

33:12.260 --> 33:13.989
SETH.
- HEY.

33:14.090 --> 33:15.432
I'M JUST CALLING
BECAUSE I THOUGHT

33:15.540 --> 33:18.839
YOU NEEDED TO KNOW
THAT AMBER'S UP HERE WITH ME.

33:18.960 --> 33:21.167
- WHAT?
WHAT IS SHE DOING THERE?

33:21.270 --> 33:22.919
- OH, GETTING OUT SOME ANGER
AT HER OLD MAN.

33:23.030 --> 33:25.578
- WELL, SHE HAD A BAD BREAKUP.

33:25.690 --> 33:28.443
- YEAH, SHE MENTIONED THAT.
- OKAY, I'LL--I'M ON THE WAY.

33:28.550 --> 33:29.756
- NO, NO, NO,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

33:29.860 --> 33:32.169
SHE'S--SHE'S SLEEPING.

33:32.280 --> 33:33.827
SHE WAS DEFINITELY UPSET
WHEN SHE GOT HERE,

33:33.940 --> 33:35.100
BUT SHE'S OKAY NOW.

33:35.220 --> 33:37.211
- SETH, HOW DID SHE EVEN
KNOW WHERE YOU ARE?

33:37.320 --> 33:38.173
I DON'T HAVE YOUR ADDRESS.

33:38.290 --> 33:40.690
- SHE JUST SHOWED UP
AT MY WORK.

33:40.810 --> 33:44.280
LISTEN, I KNOW...

33:44.400 --> 33:47.984
MY TRACK RECORD
ISN'T EXACTLY STELLAR,

33:48.090 --> 33:48.636
AND I DON'T DESERVE
THIS OPPORTUNITY,

33:48.750 --> 33:50.775
BUT I'D LIKE TO TRY.

33:50.890 --> 33:51.640
- TRY WHAT?

33:51.750 --> 33:56.369
- BE HER DAD.

33:56.480 --> 33:58.926
- YEAH.

33:59.030 --> 34:00.167
DEFINITELY.

34:00.270 --> 34:03.967
JUST TELL HER TO CALL ME, OKAY?
AND YOU CALL ME.

34:04.070 --> 34:07.062
CALL ME TOMORROW
AND TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

34:07.180 --> 34:08.579
- OF COURSE I WILL.

34:08.700 --> 34:11.976
- CALL ME TOMORROW, SETH.

34:12.080 --> 34:13.809
- HEY, SARAH, THANK YOU.

34:13.910 --> 34:15.662
BYE.

34:25.270 --> 34:26.578
- ALL RIGHT, BOYS, WHAT DO YOU
SAY WE CHANGE THE GAME

34:26.680 --> 34:29.126
TO SPICE THINGS UP
A LITTLE BIT, HUH?

34:29.230 --> 34:30.674
- PLEASE, SPICE IT UP.

34:30.790 --> 34:34.169
- THE SPICE IS JUST FINE FOR ME.
I GOTTA BE HONEST WITH YOU.

34:34.270 --> 34:35.339
- MT. EVEREST OVER HERE

34:35.450 --> 34:36.826
WANTS TO KEEP THINGS
JUST HOW THEY WERE.

34:36.930 --> 34:39.922
- DEUCES AND 55 ARE WILD.
- OOH! DIRTY DUCK 25.

34:40.040 --> 34:41.268
YES, PLEASE.
- DIRTY DUCK 25.

34:41.380 --> 34:42.312
- WE'RE GONNA PLAY WILD CARDS?

34:42.420 --> 34:43.512
WE'RE NOT PLAYING
WILD CARDS, RIGHT?

34:43.630 --> 34:45.973
- DEALER'S CHOICE.
IT'S HOUSE RULES.

34:46.080 --> 34:47.240
- YEAH, BUT THIS IS
A REAL GAME, THOUGH.

34:47.360 --> 34:48.384
WE'RE PLAYING
A REAL GAME HERE, RIGHT?

34:48.500 --> 34:49.421
- WELL, YOU KNOW,
WE LIKE TO LOOSEN IT UP

34:49.530 --> 34:50.838
TOWARDS THE END OF THE NIGHT.

34:50.950 --> 34:53.566
- WILD CARDS, THOUGH? YEAH?
- YEAH. DUCK, DUCK 25.

34:53.670 --> 34:54.568
- [sighs]

34:54.670 --> 34:55.489
- IF HE CALLS
DEUCES AND 55 WILD,

34:55.610 --> 34:57.498
DEUCES AND 55 ARE WILD.
- MM-HMM.

34:57.610 --> 34:58.918
- DOUBLE-D 25.
- WHAT ABOUT YOU?

34:59.020 --> 35:02.057
SERIOUSLY, I KNOW, LOOK,
I CALLED YOU A DONKEY BEFORE.

35:02.160 --> 35:03.400
I APOLOGIZE FOR THAT

35:03.510 --> 35:04.579
'CAUSE YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
A SERIOUS PLAYER.

35:04.680 --> 35:06.238
YOU WANT TO PLAY WILD CARDS?
- I HONESTLY DON'T CARE.

35:06.340 --> 35:07.955
SORRY.
- WELL, EVERYBODY SHOULD HAVE--

35:08.070 --> 35:08.923
SHOULD HAVE A VOTE
OR SOMETHING, RIGHT?

35:09.030 --> 35:11.271
- HANK,
WHY DON'T YOU LET IT GO?

35:11.380 --> 35:12.756
- OKAY, OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

35:12.860 --> 35:14.680
EVERYBODY'S ENTITLED TO THEIR
OPINION, BUT DEALER'S CHOICE--

35:14.800 --> 35:18.099
- JUST DEAL THE CARDS. JUST--
- WE'RE GOOD WITH WILDS.

35:18.210 --> 35:19.450
- IT'S A GAME
MY DAUGHTER COULD PLAY,

35:19.560 --> 35:21.835
BUT HOW COULD YOU NOT CARE?
- I GUESS I JUST DON'T.

35:21.940 --> 35:23.908
- OKAY, LET'S PLAY, LET'S PLAY,
LET'S PLAY. HERE WE GO.

35:24.010 --> 35:26.046
- I'M GONNA SIT THIS ONE OUT.
I'M GONNA SIT IT OUT.

35:26.150 --> 35:27.799
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE GONNA SIT THIS OUT?

35:27.910 --> 35:29.605
- I'M GONNA SIT IT OUT TOO.
- NO, NO, HEY, HEY.

35:29.710 --> 35:30.608
JOEL, DON'T SIT OUT.

35:30.710 --> 35:31.802
YOU SIT OUT
JUST 'CAUSE HE'S SITTING OUT?

35:31.920 --> 35:33.535
- JUST LET HIM SIT OUT.
JUST LET HIM SIT OUT.

35:33.640 --> 35:35.676
SOMETIMES A GUY
NEEDS TO TAKE A BREAK.

35:35.780 --> 35:38.476
- NO, SOMETIMES A GUY
SHOULDN'T TAKE A BREAK.

35:38.580 --> 35:40.127
IF A GUY--
IF THE GOING GETS TOUGH,

35:40.240 --> 35:41.502
THAT'S THE TIME TO
DOUBLE DOWN...

35:41.620 --> 35:43.019
- OH, PLEASE.
- AND YOU STAY IN IT.

35:43.140 --> 35:45.654
'CAUSE THAT'S WHEN YOU WIN.
OTHERWISE YOU LOSE YOUR SHIRT.

35:45.760 --> 35:47.489
- NEVER DOUBLE DOWN
WITH WILD CARDS.

35:47.590 --> 35:49.034
- I DON'T NEED A SPEECH. I DON'T
NEED A SPEECH, THANK YOU.

35:49.140 --> 35:51.176
I JUST--I DQJ'TMT NEED THAT.

35:51.280 --> 35:52.759
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
I'M DOING HERE.

35:52.870 --> 35:55.452
SORRY, GUYS.

35:55.560 --> 35:57.801
- JOEL.

35:57.910 --> 35:59.525
- NOBODY LIKES WILDS.

35:59.640 --> 36:00.868
- YOU KNOW WHAT,
I'M OUTTA HERE TOO.

36:00.980 --> 36:02.845
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
I DON'T NEED THIS EITHER.

36:02.950 --> 36:03.769
- LET'S JUST TAKE A BREAK.
- ALL RIGHT, WE'LL SEE YA.

36:03.880 --> 36:05.700
- WE CAN PLAY FOUR.

36:05.810 --> 36:07.050
- CROSBY, YOU WANT
TO GO TO CHEETAH'S?

36:07.160 --> 36:08.502
- I WOULD LOVE
TO GO TO CHEETAH'S,

36:08.610 --> 36:11.408
BUT I'VE GOT A BABY THAT'S GONNA
WAKE UP IN FIVE HOURS, SO...

36:11.510 --> 36:12.738
- ALL RIGHT, ANYONE ELSE?

36:12.860 --> 36:14.475
THEY GOT TWO-FOR-ONE
WELL DRINKS TONIGHT.

36:14.580 --> 36:16.502
- I'M NOT GONNA GO.
SAY HELLO TO PEPPERMINT, THOUGH.

36:16.620 --> 36:17.826
- GUYS, I'M GONNA GO TOO, MAN.
YEAH, KIDS, YOU KNOW.

36:17.930 --> 36:19.989
MIGHT AS WELL CALL IT A NIGHT.

36:20.100 --> 36:21.613
- OH, MY GOD,
THIS IS PATHETIC.

36:21.730 --> 36:24.654
I AM NEVER, EVER HAVING KIDS.
M'KAY?

36:24.760 --> 36:27.149
- GUYS, WE CAN STILL PLAY.
JUST TAKE A BREAK.

36:27.250 --> 36:28.729
- GAME'S OVER.
THROW IN THE TOWEL.

36:28.840 --> 36:31.627
[music end notes]

36:35.770 --> 36:36.737
[door slams]

36:43.680 --> 36:46.194
- THAT'S WHERE
YOU HUNG IT, HUH?

36:46.300 --> 36:48.291
- YEAH.
LOOKS GOOD THERE, RIGHT?

36:48.410 --> 36:50.332
- BE BETTER OVER THERE.

36:50.440 --> 36:52.749
PEOPLE SEE IT
AS SOON AS THEY'D COME IN THEN.

36:52.860 --> 36:54.088
- WHAT, RIGHT THERE?
WELL, THAT'S--

36:54.210 --> 36:55.654
WE GOT THE JANIS THERE ALREADY.
- YEAH...

36:55.760 --> 36:59.799
BUT THE JANIS LOOKS LIKE
SOME KID AT A CONCERT TOOK IT.

36:59.900 --> 37:01.788
- RIGHT, WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT,
WE CAN SWITCH 'EM.

37:01.900 --> 37:04.460
CROSBY'S REAL FOND
OF THAT JANIS PORTRAIT, BUT...

37:04.560 --> 37:05.697
- YEAH.
- IT'S ALL GOOD.

37:05.800 --> 37:07.688
- YOU KNOW WHAT, APOLOGIZE
TO HIM, REALLY, FOR ME.

37:07.810 --> 37:11.496
I DIDN'T MEAN TO RUIN THE GAME.
